================================================================
                  PAC-MAN for the Agon Light 2
                          @@VERSION@@
================================================================

An arcade-faithful port of the 1980 Midway / Namco PAC-MAN to
the Agon Light 2. Written in eZ80 ADL assembly.

This is an ALPHA release. Core gameplay, ghost AI, attract
rotation, sound, high scores, and DIP settings are all in.
Polish + some smaller arcade-fidelity items still in flight.


CONTENTS
--------

  PAC-MAN.BIN     The game binary (Agon Light 2)
  pacman_cfg.py   Python tool to inspect / edit PAC-MAN.CFG
  README.TXT      This file


INSTALLING ON AN AGON LIGHT 2
-----------------------------

1.  Copy PAC-MAN.BIN onto your Agon Light 2's SD card.
    Typical location: /mos/
    Filename must stay uppercase: PAC-MAN.BIN

2.  At the MOS prompt, run:

        run PAC-MAN.BIN

3.  On first boot the game creates PAC-MAN.CFG next to the
    binary. It stores DIP settings and the high-score table.
    Defaults work fine — you don't have to touch it.


RUNNING UNDER THE EMULATOR
--------------------------

If you don't have hardware, fab-agon-emulator works well.
Drop PAC-MAN.BIN into a folder, then:

    fab-agon-emulator --sdcard ./ --vdp vdp_console8.so

  https://github.com/tomm/fab-agon-emulator


CONTROLS
--------

  Arrow keys      Move Pac-Man
  C               Insert a credit
  1               Start a one-player game
  2               Start a two-player game (when 2+ credits)
  P               Pause
  Esc             Quit


SETTINGS + HIGH SCORES (PAC-MAN.CFG)
------------------------------------

The included Python tool inspects and edits the file:

    python pacman_cfg.py dump PAC-MAN.CFG
    python pacman_cfg.py edit PAC-MAN.CFG --lives 5
    python pacman_cfg.py edit PAC-MAN.CFG --show-score-table on

The high-score table itself is read-only via the tool (use
the game to set new scores). Run with no arguments for help.


